1
00:00:29,863 --> 00:00:31,072
Are you okay?

2
00:00:32,490 --> 00:00:33,241
Yeah

3
00:00:34,284 --> 00:00:35,118
Thank you

4
00:00:37,746 --> 00:00:39,164
Looks like you have bad luck today,

5
00:00:39,706 --> 00:00:40,665
seeing you got hurt

6
00:00:42,042 --> 00:00:42,709
Huh?

7
00:00:44,878 --> 00:00:45,128
Oh

8
00:00:46,004 --> 00:00:46,963
The scratch on your hand

9
00:00:53,094 --> 00:00:53,636
Huh?

10
00:00:54,387 --> 00:00:55,638
When did I get this scratch?

11
00:00:57,557 --> 00:00:59,517
Oh, hold on

12
00:01:12,238 --> 00:01:14,199
It's a good thing I had a Band-Aid with me

13
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:17,160
Thank you

14
00:01:20,955 --> 00:01:22,916
I want to thank you,

15
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:23,958
so would you like a cup of coffee...

16
00:01:24,167 --> 00:01:25,001
- Minu

17
00:01:25,210 --> 00:01:26,377
- Where are the coffee beans?

18
00:01:27,670 --> 00:01:29,255
All right, sir. I'll be right there

19
00:01:33,843 --> 00:01:34,636
Huh?

20
00:01:37,138 --> 00:01:38,348
Where'd he go?

21
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:46,189
What a strange guy

22
00:02:15,927 --> 00:02:17,428
Hey, why did you come home so late?

23
00:02:18,346 --> 00:02:20,056
I came straight home from work

24
00:02:20,765 --> 00:02:21,432
And,

25
00:02:21,808 --> 00:02:23,101
I was a bit late buying this

26
00:02:23,852 --> 00:02:24,519
This

27
00:02:24,978 --> 00:02:26,146
smells like raw meat

28
00:02:28,189 --> 00:02:29,065
Ta-da

29
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:30,066
It's beef tartare

30
00:02:32,777 --> 00:02:34,154
You finally have

31
00:02:34,445 --> 00:02:35,697
something to celebrate

32
00:02:38,908 --> 00:02:39,325
What

33
00:02:39,868 --> 00:02:40,869
am I celebrating?

34
00:02:42,495 --> 00:02:44,038
You're not sick these days

35
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:46,583
And

36
00:02:47,458 --> 00:02:49,002
it's my payday today

37
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:52,755
Gosh, it feels like forever since my last payday

38
00:02:53,631 --> 00:02:55,341
How great would it be to win the lottery, too?

39
00:02:57,802 --> 00:02:59,554
Don’t chase empty dreams

40
00:03:01,014 --> 00:03:02,307
What would you know, vampire?

41
00:03:03,224 --> 00:03:04,392
Just dig in

42
00:03:13,943 --> 00:03:14,611
Oh

43
00:03:15,486 --> 00:03:16,654
This is seriously good!

44
00:03:17,405 --> 00:03:18,239
Right?

45
00:03:18,907 --> 00:03:20,658
Human food isn't all bad, you see!

46
00:03:21,951 --> 00:03:23,953
Perhaps your palate is slowly changing

47
00:03:25,622 --> 00:03:26,372
Whatever

48
00:03:26,664 --> 00:03:28,041
Just pour me a drink already

49
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:31,753
Okay

50
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:34,380
I'll pour an amazing somaek cocktail

51
00:03:42,597 --> 00:03:43,556
Here you go

52
00:03:45,767 --> 00:03:46,517
Cheers

53
00:03:46,559 --> 00:03:47,018
Cheers

54
00:03:47,477 --> 00:03:48,478
Cheers!

55
00:03:56,903 --> 00:03:57,695
Oh?

56
00:03:59,113 --> 00:03:59,739
What

57
00:04:00,031 --> 00:04:01,032
is this?

58
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:03,701
Oh, this?

59
00:04:05,286 --> 00:04:06,704
It's just a little scratch from work,

60
00:04:07,038 --> 00:04:08,373
and someone put this on for me

61
00:04:09,624 --> 00:04:10,792
Who?

62
00:04:12,669 --> 00:04:14,837
He was very handsome,

63
00:04:15,838 --> 00:04:16,506
and...

64
00:04:16,714 --> 00:04:18,049
he had a mystical vibe

65
00:04:19,801 --> 00:04:22,345
Like someone straight out of a K-drama!

66
00:04:23,805 --> 00:04:24,639
So,

67
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:28,101
did you fall for that handsome guy or something?

68
00:04:30,436 --> 00:04:31,854
What's with you?

69
00:04:31,854 --> 00:04:33,356
I'm just thankful, that's all

70
00:04:34,732 --> 00:04:36,276
Don't trust handsome guys

71
00:04:36,776 --> 00:04:38,319
They're mostly twisted on the inside

72
00:04:42,031 --> 00:04:43,157
What's going on with you?

73
00:04:46,077 --> 00:04:46,703
Hey,

74
00:04:47,245 --> 00:04:48,538
are you jealous?

75
00:04:49,706 --> 00:04:51,332
What do you mean I'm jealous?

76
00:04:51,457 --> 00:04:54,294
If you get hurt, it complicates things for me

77
00:04:56,713 --> 00:04:57,588
Oh,

78
00:04:58,131 --> 00:04:59,424
I see how it is

79
00:05:03,219 --> 00:05:05,805
And if something like that happens, call me

80
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:08,308
I can make it better for you

81
00:05:11,602 --> 00:05:12,770
Then,

82
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:15,481
you can put it on me instead next time

83
00:05:24,449 --> 00:05:25,950
Still, don't get hurt

84
00:05:26,576 --> 00:05:28,077
I don't like seeing you get hurt

85
00:05:31,664 --> 00:05:32,665
Okay

86
00:05:35,168 --> 00:05:36,085
Gosh

87
00:05:37,128 --> 00:05:38,880
I think we drank too much

88
00:05:40,089 --> 00:05:41,924
I'm gonna go to the bathroom real quick

89
00:05:59,692 --> 00:06:01,277
Hey...

90
00:06:03,404 --> 00:06:05,615
I don't exactly know what I'm feeling right now,

91
00:06:07,283 --> 00:06:09,410
but if I don't express it right now,

92
00:06:10,995 --> 00:06:12,330
I feel like I'll regret it forever

93
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:35,556
- What... is this emotion?

94
00:08:37,141 --> 00:08:40,603
- Unfamiliar, yet familiar

95
00:08:43,731 --> 00:08:45,816
- This emotion right now

96
00:08:46,275 --> 00:08:48,110
- is inexplicable

97
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:50,988
- Is it because of his blood?

98
00:08:51,656 --> 00:08:52,657
- Or

99
00:08:52,865 --> 00:08:55,243
- have I really come to love this human?

100
00:08:55,785 --> 00:08:57,411
- I cannot know,

101
00:08:58,079 --> 00:09:00,957
- but I want to cherish this moment right now

102
00:09:02,583 --> 00:09:03,251
- Is this

103
00:09:04,085 --> 00:09:05,378
- what you call "love"?
